Refound the republic around the socialism of the 21st century.
This is the joint project of Venezuelan Hugo Chávez, Bolivian Evo Morales and Ecuadorian Rafael Correa.
This Sunday, like its counterparts and friends, was the third one to put to the vote a draft new Constitution.
Mission accomplished since 64% of voters voted "yes" to the referendum, according to official results covering 80% of votes.
