The Benelux governments nationalize part of the Fortis bank
The Benelux states are helping the Belgian-Dutch bank, as the first European banking institution in distress as a result of the snowball effect of the credit market crisis in the United States, partly nationalizing it. The three countries are supporting, at an amount of EUR 11.2 billion, this financial and insurance institution also having interests in Hungary.
