In accordance with the decision taken on Sunday night, the three states will purchase nearly half (49%) of the bank's capital in each of the countries.
The bank will undoubtedly sell part of its shares, including, first of all, the activities, essentially insurance, that it acquired last year from the Dutch organization ABN Amro.
